Ikeja Electric Distribution Company (IKEDC), at the weekend, commenced the rollout of the National Mass Metering Programme (NMMP) in Victory Estate, Ago Palace Way, Okota area of Lagos State.
 
The programme is part of the Federal Government’s effort to bridge the country’s metering gap and also cushion the effect of the Service Reflective Tariff on electricity consumers.   To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .